        <div class="content">
            <h2>Steps to Becoming a Pediatric Nurse</h2>
            <p>To become a pediatric nurse, you need to follow several steps, including earning a nursing degree, obtaining a nursing license, and gaining experience in pediatric care.</p>
            <img src="data:image/jpeg;base64," alt="Nursing Education">
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Education:</strong> Complete a nursing program (ADN or BSN) from an accredited institution.</li>
                <li><strong>Licensing:</strong> Pass the NCLEX-RN exam to become a licensed registered nurse (RN).</li>
                <li><strong>Experience:</strong> Gain experience in a pediatric healthcare setting.</li>
                <li><strong>Certification:</strong> Consider obtaining certification in pediatric nursing (e.g., CPN or RN-BC).</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
